# No push to live site

**Never** push, publish, or deploy changes to the live site. The user handles that themselves.

## Forbidden

- `git push` (to any remote, including `origin`)
- `gh` commands that publish (e.g. `gh pr merge`, releases that go live)
- Deploy scripts, GitHub Actions triggers, or hosting CLI deploys meant to update production
- Offering to push or deploy as a follow-up unless the user explicitly asks in that message

## Allowed

- Edit source files and run `./sync-docs.sh` to copy into `docs/` locally
- `git add`, `git commit`, and other local git work **only when the user explicitly asks**
- Tell the user their changes are ready and that they can commit/push when they want

## If deployment is needed

Only run push or deploy commands when the user **explicitly** requests it in that message. Otherwise, never.
